{
  "design_notes": "The Intro Wave introduces the driving rhythm of the synthwave track, utilizing low-density placements on high-pitch lead notes and introducing a single 1.0-beat hold on the synth sustain. The Main Theme Build mirrors the alternating energy of the song's mid-section, creating an intense wave-like density pattern where high-energy even bars use rapid cascading subdivisions and lower-energy odd bars breathe with basic quarter-note grids. The Outro Decline escalates to the peak energy of the track with a dense cascade and sustain, followed by a dramatic drop in density to allow the music to fade out cleanly and let the player experience the relaxation of the final bars.",
  "sections": [
    {
      "name": "Intro Wave",
      "start_bar": 0,
      "intent": "Introduce the groove with clean, spaced-out high-band hits, establishing the melody's outline."
    },
    {
      "name": "Main Theme Build",
      "start_bar": 5,
      "intent": "Deliver alternating high/low density waves that follow the per-bar energy spikes."
    },
    {
      "name": "Outro Decline",
      "start_bar": 10,
      "intent": "Reach the peak energy cascade before dropping density to let the outro breathe fully."
    }
  ],
